  "id": 1864,
  "name": "Pilgrimage Church of Wies",
  "description": "Miraculously preserved in the beautiful setting of an Alpine valley, the Church of Wies (1745&ndash;54), the work of architect Dominikus Zimmermann, is a masterpiece of Bavarian Rococo &ndash; exuberant, colourful and joyful.",
