  "id": 212,
  "name": "Djémila",
  "description": "Situated 900 m above sea-level, Dj&eacute;mila, or Cuicul, with its forum, temples, basilicas, triumphal arches and houses, is an interesting example of Roman town planning adapted to a mountain location.",
