  "name": "Coro and its Port",
  "description": "With its earthen constructions unique to the Caribbean, Coro is the only surviving example of a rich fusion of local traditions with Spanish Mud&eacute;jar and Dutch architectural techniques. One of the first colonial towns (founded in 1527), it has some 602 historic buildings.",
